						               													<description>An interesting cross between ccgs, rpgs and board games: the game contains a board, cardboard pawns, character cards, dice, cards, but the cards are different in each box. New decks of cards can be bought to increase the variety (in fact the recommended number of cards for a deck of one player is 60-80, but the box itself contains only 50 cards).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game is set in the world of a series of Hungarian fantasy novels.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;At the beginning of the game every player chooses a team of characters. There are cards with the characters' abilities. Then in his/her turn the player rolls two dice, the result is the amont of action points, which can be used to put the characters on the board, move them, draw new cards, or build some kind of energy plant. The energy given by the plants can be used to play cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
